news.title: Majority of shopping, commercial complexes in Prayagraj sans safety audit
news.para: Hemant Sharma, assistant director, electrical safety directorate (Prayagraj zone) told TOI, “Majority of commercial establishments in the city have not obtained NOC ( No Objection Certificate) from the Electrical safety directorate till now.

news.title: Pune: June 30 last date to avail property tax concessions
news.para: Tax defaulters will also get another month to clear their dues. They have till April 30 to pay the tax for the 2022-2023 financial year.

news.title: Allotment letters for Atal flats likely by April 10: Ludhiana improvement trust
news.para: LIT chiarman Tarsem Bhinder informed that the letters would be handed over on April 10 in a function where local bodies minister Inderbir Singh Nijjar would preside over as chief guest.

news.title: Rajasthan RERA fines builder for changing sale deed
news.para: Rajasthan RERA further held that the allottee is not required to wait for resale of the cancelled booking of the flat for getting the refund from the promoter.

news.title: Construction of fourth floor to put extra burden on infrastructure, say RWAs at protest in Gurugram
news.para: At the meeting, residents unanimously decided to oppose the policy and demanded a complete ban on the stilt plus four floors in the city. They also highlighted the problem being faced by them due to provision of increased floor area ratio (FAR).

news.title: Kotak Mahindra Life Insurance leases 1.5 lakh sq ft space in Tata Realty's tower
news.para: The company will be paying rentals of ₹100 per sq ft a month, bringing its total pay-out to ₹162 crore over the term of the lease, excluding the rental escalations. The agreement includes a clause to increase rentals by 15% every three years.

news.title: Over 35 builders in Greater Noida West to be booked for water theft
news.para: In July last year, a district-level joint committee, comprising the district magistrate and officials from the state and central pollution control boards, was formed in the wake of petitions by two environmentalists alleging that 63 residential projects of around 40 builders were extracting groundwater illegally.

news.title: Navi Mumbai builder to refund homebuyer with 12% interest & pay Rs 2 lakh in relief
news.para: The Thane Additional District Consumer Dispute Redressal Commission also directed Ajit Singh of Prathamesh Construction to pay a compensation of Rs 2 lakh for deficiency in service and unfair trade practice.

news.title: Maharashtra SOS to centre as ED probe stalls SRA projects
news.para: There are nearly 12.5 lakh slum units in the city, housing 62 lakh residents. Since its formation 23 years ago, the SRA has provided new apartments to around 2.1 lakh families.

news.title: Fundraising via REITs, InvITs hits all-time low in FY23 on higher yields on debt, lack of new launches
news.para: ​Going forward, a change in the tax rule on distributions classified as repayment could lead to a substantial increase in tax liability as it will be taxed as 'other income' in the hands of the investor, making the instruments less attractive, Manavi Prabhu, Head Fixed Income, Anand Rathi Shares and Stock Brokers, said.

news.title: Visakhapatnam civic body collects record Rs 421 crore in property tax
news.para: This is the highest ever tax revenue realised by the Vizag civic body. By doing so, the GVMC surpassed its self-target of 375 crore tax collections for the 2023 fiscal.

news.title: At Rs 633 crore, Navi Mumbai civic body breaks its property tax collection record
news.para: By March 31, the civic body surpassed all previous year property tax collections and recorded Rs107.17 crore higher than last fiscal. The total collection of property tax in 2022-23 stood at Rs 633.17 crore against Rs 526 crore of the year 2021-22.

news.title: Hyderabad civic body's property tax collection up by 10%, but misses target again
news.para: However, overall property tax collection was more than last year by 10%. The civic body has assessed 13.53 lakh properties across the city, 7% more compared to 2021-22.

news.title: Patna civic body collects Rs 105 crore as property tax
news.para: Patna Municipal Corporation (PMC) has now planned to catch hold of such residential premises who have electricity connection but are not paying holding tax. It has also urged the residents to pay their taxes in the first three months for the current year and avail 5% rebate.

news.title: Civic body comes up with IDs of 5,000 new properties in Chandigarh
news.para: Since, matching of the records of electricity and estate office data with property tax is still going on, this number of 5,000 new properties will increase manifold in the coming days when the exercise is done by the MC.
